Installation and Activation of remote station by Andreas Münchow and Thorsten Zieke. VSAT works stable but seiscomp-pc is sometimes off. Solar power doesn’t seem to be sufficient?!
Power - VSAT online but problems with solar power. Unconfirmed information that one battery is “bloated”.
Station ist working properly since then. The problems was a bad connections from the solarcontroller to the battery.
VSAT online, but station seems to have problems with solar power again. Somebody need to go there and check the power supply.
Pak Sunaryo at station to check the problem. Now the VSAT router is offline too.
Power System unstable - to fix problems I replaced fuses and also upgraded the T.E. and BGAN.

The VSAT is offline again. Local staff said the router is broken. Only the “Power” Led is on, but all other LED at the router are off. This is the second router in an short period. Need for a check of router power supply in JAGI
The equipment for the solarupdate, an new router and new 12V/24V router power supply was send to Jajag.
JAGI was very often offline because the solarpower was not enough. We installed two more solarmodules. We had diodes inside the powercollectrobox and inside the TE. I removed the ones.
Station again offline. VSAT seems to create CRC errors on the sat network, meaning the router has still power but doesn't work properly. Maybe BUC or router problem.

VSAT-System Since 6 days the station is offline. Via BGAN we can login, but the router can not be pinged. The power supply is ok. When we activate the router we get error messages which disturb the hole VSAT network. So we switched the router off from hub side. The LAN connection seems to be bad too. Michael will go there on Christmas.
VSAT-System. Exchanged both, BUC and Router. Station online. (Strange: the router had a wrong IP. Who did this to me!?).
Power - Outage every night. Station online over the day but offline at night. Sometimes goes off after 24h on again. Power problem. Can somebody please fix this power thing!?

Solar. Stations VSAT system now stable, but the inner power cycle is going off 7 hours daily leaving data gaps. Seems like a battery or one solar module is not working anymore as outages occur always at night, while the VSAT is running without problem.
Update. They installed new solarpanels to update the JAGI station to full solar.(Type2) But they did not connect the solar power with the station. This will be done at the next visit.

TE. After Yudha installed the solarupdate in Juli we did exchange the TE(Typ1) with an TE(Typ2). We also checked the Solarpower for Sensors, because the station did die at night. But everything seems to be fine, we could not find any problem.

The station was temporarly set up in the BMG-office of Palembang. Because the bunker was not yet finished. Everything was build up without Gitews VSAT-Equipment. We did use the BMG VSAT.

GPS. Jay set up the GPS station in Palembang. He used an outdoor rack for his equipment. Together with Michael they installed and activated the Gitews VSAT- Equipment. But our equipment is not yet connected with that network.
Station went offline, no reason known.
Defect power supply was exchanged, station immediately online again.

Fibervault. The GFZ Fiberbunker was installed. This needed 4 days. Now the station is ready to be moved to the new permanent place. The GPS Station was not working since around 4 weeks. I checked it and the fuse(2.5A) of the PPU was open. I closed it but 2 days later it was open again. So I changed the plug to another plug of the PPU with an 10A fuse.There was no data of the seism. Station. So I went there to see what is wrong. But everything was fine. Even the satellite connection worked well. So I called Jakarta and agreed. And found an problem in the configuration of the station in Jakarta. That was done be Andres.

The seismic station was moved from the temporary place to the permanent place. The STS2 was installed in the Fiberbunker and the electronic in the shelter from BMKG. The router was moved to the shelter of the seismic equipment and seismic station was activated. New coax cabling between router and dish.
The VSAT-Router stopped working and Pak Kusnadi plugged the jack for the main power from X1 at the PPU to the X3. VSAT went online again. So it is now secured with an 10A fuse.
VSAT was off again at the station. After a remote 'reset' from the HUB it is online again.
Seismic vault flooded. Both BB sensor and Accelerometer under water. Wolfgang and Yanuar at station to install both sensors in the shelter and to check if vault can be fixed.
We repaired the fibervault. We now want to wait if the vault is still dry in half a year. Then we want to move the STS2 back into the fibervault.
The VSAT router is offline again. We often have problems with that router. It needs to be exchanged.
Mr Hasyim try to restart i Direct Router by pull out powercable.Couse the router maybe hang
Mr.Kusnadi try restart by pull out powercable. it is two way.

We moved the STS2 from the Shelter to the fibervault, to get an better seismic signal. After we did move the STS2 we did not get any signal from the STS2 again. Seems like the conector inside the STS2 is coroded from the time in the water last year. We need to exchange the STS2. We did also install an new BUC and Router, because we had the same problems like one year ago. The station is going offline and needs to be restart from Jakarta.

Micha Heute war SAUI kurz offline. Ich habe mich dann über BGAN eingeloggt und wir konnten den Router anpingen. Micha hat sich dann mit telnet IP_Router eigeloggt. Es sah alles gut aus. RX TX waren in Ordnung. Aber der Router hat keine Befehle über den RX empfangen. Man konnte also keinen reboot von remote machen. Nachdem wir den reboot lokal gemacht hatten hat der Router sich direkt wieder eingeloggt.

Saui ist wieder offline. Wenn wir uns über das BGAN einloggen können wir vom SeisComP nicht pingen. Das heißt, der Router steht vollkommen. Ich habe mit Hilfe der TE die Spannungs- und Stromwerte ausgelesen und diese sind oke. 24V bei 1.9A. Noch wissen wir nicht was es ist. Wir werden versuchen einen harten reset zu machen. Mit Hilfe der TE oder den Leuten vor Ort.
Wir haben mit Saui telefoniert, und der Router ist voll mit Ameisen, sie werden ihn jetzt säubern, und wir hoffen. Mit Baygon und kapur ajaib.

Saui is still offline. Sie haben den Router mit Druckluft ausgeblassen und die Ameisen sind alle weg. Leider ist der Router danach trotzdem nicht online gegangen. Wahrscheinlich müssen wir ihn jetzt austauschen.

Solar We got the news the solarpanels where stolen. So we went there and change the system to normal power. So SOEI is now the first station that is only running with normal power. Michael said the seismic datastream was dead before the VSAT connection was down. That strange because the sensors have an bigger batteriepuffer, and should work for around 1 week without any mainspower. Whereas the VSAT-System has an puffer for around 1 day only
PPU Ikhsan was at the station. He exchanged the F02 fuse at the PPU. The station is online again. Chrictec is now changed to X3 at the PPU.

The station is set up. Because of the VSAT problems not yet online.
VSAT-System was installed and IP configuration adjusted to VSAT-System. It was quiet difficult because the distance from antenna to router is about 100m.

TX - Signal from Router was broken. They exchanged the router to see if it was a malfunction at the router. The router seems to be ok. Afterwards the cables from BUC and LNB to router were checked(TX and RX interchanged). The cables seems to be ok. It looks like the BUC is broken. At the next journey they want to exchange the BUC with a new one.They took the router to Jakarta.
The BUC was defect.2W C-Band BUC SSPBM-C2-DSE from Advantech P/N 13C-03B021-1M0S s/n H5970 was exchanged with the same type. s/n: H5971 new P/N 13C-03B021-1M0S.
Station online but unstable. Reason unknown most probably power.

Installed new cable connectors and exchanged Advantech BUC (5W) against Belcom BUC (2W). TX power with Advantech BUC -5.8 dbm. TX power with Belcom BUC -´12dbm! Also feed was exchanged (interface RG8 cable against interface waveguide). Station online and seems stable.– BUC “2W C-Band BUC SSPBM-C2-DSE from Advantech P/N 13C-03B021-1M0S s/n H5971” and Feeder was exchanged. New BUC type, Belcom BLC-2-F SN: 1067720783
Station stable online but TX RX characteristics slowly degrading. RG11 cables are at max lengths with around 100m.
UGM was offline for one day. Someone from BMKG office Yogjakarta went there and did something. Unfortunately we dont know what. But the station is online again.

A team from BMKG installed solarpanels for the stations. The power will be enough to run the station on sunny days. They installed 12 80W panels. I installed the TE, DFT1 and the BGAN. The station is now complete.
The SeisComP Box was defect. It was ecchanged with an new one (sn:AW 6036 0308 22). It seems like that the harddisk was defect at the old SeisComP Box. He will be repaired.
He installed the new SC-Box in UGM. But we can not ping to the 172.16.80.34.
The trees in front of the BGAN already cut. The BMKG technician said all status LED on SeisComP box are oke.
SeisComP can be pinged from office and from 192.168.77.0(sc-aqui).
mengganti BUC, mengganti hard disk pada perangkat seiscomp box namun perangkat seiscomp box masih sering hang dan diputuskan seiscomp tersebut dibawa ke BMKG Jakarta untuk diperiksa.

No data since 1.5 days. The NET LED at the iDirect Router did flash orange. And the iDirect Router was offline. BMKG Yogja did an hardreset by pulling out the power connector. After this the Router was online again.

In /home/sysop/templates/plugins.ini_gitews.tpl #sid_z# exchanged with 9. This was done because the Z-Channel was defined with modbus address 8. But it has to be 9. An other possibilty is to add an extra channel in front of the Z-channel in the keyfile.
